PLAY WAS STOPPED WHEN A PASS FROM INSIDE A TEAMS DEFENDING ZONE CROSSED 
THE CENTRE LINE WITH A FACEOFF HELD IN THE DEFENDING ZONE OF THE 
OFFENDING TEAM NOW THE CENTRE LINE IS NO LONGER USED IN THE NHL TO 
DETERMINE A TWOLINE PASS INFRACTION A CHANGE THAT THE IIHF HAD ADOPTED IN 
PLAYERS ARE NOW ABLE TO PASS TO TEAMMATES WHO ARE MORE THAN THE BLUE AND 
